    <string name="menu_pip_adb_title">Unlock PiP via ADB</string>
    <string name="dialog_pip_adb_guide_title">Picture-in-Picture ADB Guide</string>
    <string name="dialog_pip_adb_guide_text"><![CDATA[
Some TV manufacturers block Picture-in-Picture (PiP) by default. Follow these steps to permanently unlock it:<br><br>
1. Enable Developer Options on the TV (click "Build number" 7 times in system settings).<br>
2. Enable "ADB debugging" in Developer Options.<br>
3. Open a command prompt on your PC and connect to the TV:<br>
<tt><b>adb connect [YOUR_TV_IP]:5555</b></tt><br><br>
4. Copy and execute the following command exactly:<br>
<tt><b>adb shell appops set com.shipofagony.klippshell4creality PICTURE_IN_PICTURE allow</b></tt><br><br>
5. Restart the KlippShell app on your TV. PiP is now permanently ready to use!
]]></string>

