    <string name="welcome_tile_title">Welcome to KlippShell! 👋</string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_msg">Great to have you here! To help you get the most out of your printer monitoring, here is a brief overview of KlippShell\'s core features and some TV specific requirements. KlippShell is designed to run smoothly on smartphones, tablets, or user-friendly on Android TV.\n\n1️⃣ FIRST STEPS\nAdd your first 3D printer below. Currently, almost all models available on the market are included. If you want to use another Klipper-based printer, you can choose \"Custom Model\".\nNote: Depending on your printer model and network configuration, you might need to adjust your ports and camera paths manually to guarantee perfect monitoring. However, the automatic network scan should handle most configurations on its own.\n⚠️ If you don\'t get a live image of the printer, please visit https://github.com/DnG-Crafts/K2-Camera and install the FIX. Unfortunately, this requires root rights on the printer!\n💡 Tip: Long-pressing one of your saved printers in the main menu opens options to switch the default view between live stream monitoring and Klipper OS, or to delete this printer.\n\n2️⃣ SMART LIVE CONTROL\nIn video stream mode, you control everything via three main buttons at the bottom:\n• Left button: Opens the menu for On-Screen Display (OSD), video zoom, PiP, enclosure lighting, screensaver, and aspect ratio.\n• Middle button: Seamlessly switches between Klipper OS (Dashboard) and the pure camera live stream.\n• Right button: Safely returns you to the main menu at any time.\n\n3️⃣ AUTOSTART MODE\nIf you have already successfully configured a printer, you can enable autostart mode in the settings. This allows you to jump right into the live stream view as soon as the app starts.\n\n4️⃣ COMPANION MODE\nWith KlippShell, you can use your device as a TV dashboard (Master) or as a smartphone remote control (Slave). Activate companion mode in the settings to comfortably control your TV from your smartphone.\n\n5️⃣ PICTURE-IN-PICTURE (PiP)\nAlthough KlippShell fully supports PiP, some TV manufacturers refuse to offer this feature natively. Don\'t worry: in the settings, you will find an advanced feature with precise instructions on how to unlock PiP on your TV via a simple ADB command!\n\n6️⃣ TV \"NOW LIVE\" FUNCTION\nIf you want to use the \"Now Live\" TV function, manufacturer restrictions might prevent it from showing natively on your TV dashboard. In this case, we recommend using an alternative TV launcher like \"Projectivity Launcher\" on your TV device to fully enjoy this feature.</string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_btn">Got it &amp; Hide</string>

